reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great quality. Love them.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars If you love organization, this is a MUST
reviews.reviewText: I have trouble keeping my sheet sets together and keeping them organized and looking good in my closet and this is a DREAM. Easy to use, I love the little clear display window so you can see what set is in there and there is plenty of room for a lot of sheets. Also it's a great space saver if you have limited space, I had my sheets in baskets before and now I have extra space to store other things with all the room it has saved. I bought an additional set because I loved them so much.

Who can fold a fitted sheet? Not this girl. Always looked like it was a balled up mess! I had about 6 sets of sheets taking up a full laundry basket in my linen closet. Ordered these and they saved me so much room now! Not to mention no more balled up mess. I will buy more when I add more sheets to my collection. One of the zippers was broken though when I opened up but that’s the only downfall.

reviews.reviewTitle: At Last!! No more mismatched bed linen!
reviews.reviewText: These storage units fit a full queen size sheet set (fitted, plain, 2 pillow cases) & a queen comforter cover set (cover & 2 pillow cases) very comfortably. Pls note these are cotton sheets, not flannel. It does the same for double beds.King bed sets will pack comfortably in them, but you would have to pack your comforters separately.Genius product for queen and doubles to pack sheets sets and matching comforters in a single box to avoid mismatching linen! Absolute treasure. I have since ordered more!

Overall, the boxes are not bad. They were not really big enough to correctly fit queen sized duvet covers. This makes the box bulge. I would recommend King size. The zipper is very stiff. You need to soap the zipper and go slow so it doesn't jam. The velcro is not sewn on super well. I expect they will come off soon.The boxes were a decent price and they did the trick. I am not sure what other products are like. I would use these again for spare items but not for anything I am in at least once a week. I am thinking of getting more for craft projects. It would be nice to pull 'project' off the shelf and go.

I like these sheet boxes. They are large enough to hold king size sheets. You have to fold them just right to get into the box. Rolling doesn't work. I like the open window to see the colours. I hand wrote signs on the cards they provided. They do take up a lot of space but it is neat and tidy to store them.
